sub_fields.message: On layout order, if the image is on the right, in mobile, it is moved to the top of the group, so the text will follow. Whereas if the image is on the left, it will naturally be in the correct order when in mobile.

sub_fields.label: Help -- Button Examples and Tips (click to expand)
Inline Hero Button Help
sub_fields.message:
To the right are examples of buttons themed for the website. You can add these easily by creating an anchor tag with a class, using one specified. This will add all the styling around the button. Please don't forget the title! Example:

<a href="/blog/" class="btn brand-cta-white" title="description" >Learn More</a>

<a href="/blog/" class="btn brand-cta-red" title="description" >Learn More</a>

The description should be something other than Learn More. The caret ">" is added via CSS, no need to do anything with that.

sub_fields.label: About the Finishes layout
sub_fields.message: This is sweet because you select what finishes to include and they are built out.

sub_fields.label: Select My Product Finishes
sub_fields.name: finishes
sub_fields.instructions: You are provided with the names of all the finishes available. Select which go with this product. Please let Greg know for finishes you wish to add.

sub_fields.label: Value Proposition
sub_fields.name: value_proposition
sub_fields.instructions: The key is to not write too much. Please keep it long enough but not to exceed the height of the opposite side. If you want to make your link appear as a button, I suggest using the following class value: <a href="/blog/" class="cta-brand btn mx-auto" target="">SUBMIT</a>

sub_fields.label: Finish Chip
sub_fields.name: finish_chip
sub_fields.instructions:
Set the shape and style of the finish chip, from round to rectangular, show or hide the drop-shadow. 
Ideas: 90, 50, 0 -> for a wide rectangular look. If you have just a few, finishes, go with: 90, 90, 50 for a big round puck. If you have several, 60, 60, 50 is a great combo.

sub_fields.label: Chip border-radius
sub_fields.name: chip_border_radius
sub_fields.instructions: Zero gives a square look whereas a high number returns the round appearance.

sub_fields.label: About Headings
sub_fields.message: In web semantics, we should have one H1 on the page followed by an organization of headings and sub-headings like when you outlined stories in elementary school. On these pages, the H1 is the title and the rest of the content is organized under that. This organization helps your SEO. If you feel you need larger H2 and such, let's work on that.
